reviewText: It didn't include the gasket seal! Vitally important for installation. My husband had to make extra trips to hardware store and spend another $12 on top of buying this so we'd have all the parts. Pretty dishonest to sell a kit without all parts.
summary: Pretty dishonest to sell a kit without all parts

reviewText: The pre-formed ferrule broke right off while I was finger tightening the nut onto the union. Thank goodness it happened then. I am a skilled person, so this was no ham handed homeowner mistake. I can have no comfort in this product now and won't try to use it.
summary: Beware. This stuff is very weak.

reviewText: Rated 1 star because the box showed an oboe reed case on it, but a saxophone reed case was packed inside.  Rico should hire people who know the difference.  We returned the purchase to Amazon and bought an oboe reed case elsewhere.
summary: Wrong reed case packed in oboe reed case box

reviewText: I received this with my purchase of a InSinkErator Evolution.  A standard faucet of water into the sink causes it to back up and trying to get any thing larger than a pea through it can be a dangerous operation. Not recommended.

Got this with an InSinkerator Evolution. Worst feature about the new garbage disposal. It barely drains water, and its impossible for waste to get past it. You literally need to push the waste past it with a spoon. will be replacing soon.
summary: Don't buy one if you want to actually be able to use your garbage disposal.

reviewText: This design is focused 100% of sound insulation, but does so by sacrificing water and food flow.  If you want your sink to constantly back up and be pushing food and other items through this collar manually, by all means buy this.  I got this for free with my new disposal and absolutely can't stand it.  A single PEA can block the drainage.
summary: Restricted water flow and constant clogs.

reviewText: using this adapter lowers the profile and draining way too much. with that you must spend more money on proper draining. I finally used the ez mount system that came with the Waste King. I wasted time and money on the adapter
summary: I finally used the ez mount system that came with the Waste King. I wasted time and money on the

reviewText: This is probably my 4th one Ive usijg over the years.  Product has CHANGED and the food does not pass through at all!  I must shove the food through manually everytime which is dangerous when the disposal is operating.  Only thing that passes through is water!

This didn't even make it a year...all pliability is gone and food scraps have to be forced through it using your hands.
Why can't they make one from silicone material?
I will be searching for another brand or manufacturer.

Don't bother buying this with your new Waste King even though Amazon suggests you need it with their "others also bought this".  You won't need it.  My installer said he hasn't ever needed it when replacing an old disposal.  You might need it if new install.
summary: Don't need if installing disposal replacement.

reviewText: I bought this to make sure I had a replacement ready when the original wore out. They always do. This is a very cheap looking version of the original. I had to buy a new disposal and bought a 1 hp Waste King The one I replace was an Insinkerator 333 model. That top piece  fits the Waste  King. I will buy an Insinkerator splash guard to replace when this wears out

Rigid and water drainage is extremely slow. I called waste king and they were not aware of any problems, but they sent me a replacement that actually works. The replacement splash guard is softer and water drains  appropriately.
summary: Call waste king for replacement if you have slow drainage

reviewText: Crap filter.  The original lasted great for 3 years till it was lost in a move.  This one?  After a lousy 3 weeks it started having issues of refusing to absorb water up for the humidifier to release in the air.
summary: Waste of $.  Lasts 2-3 weeks and then you will have to replace it.

reviewText: If I could give this a negative star...I would!!  We couldn't even get the included tank filled because it's junk...they would not fill it. This came with pieces broken and pieces that needed modified. Only plus side is it kept the beer cold!!

Watch out! this filter pops up as a replacement for the Sunbeam Model SCM3609 but it is 3-4 inches shorter than the needed filter size. The Amazon filter link doesn't work very well; I had to google Sunbeam filter SCM3609 and then Amazon showed the correct filters.
summary: Does not fit the dual tank Sunbeam Humidifier

reviewText: Had this unit 3 months. Leaked out 4 2.5 lb tanks. Teflon taped all connections, made sure all gaskets were in correctly and even had system evaluated by professional bar tender. System is going back to the retailer today and going back to a small bar refrigerator. Very sorry I even purchased this unit. Not worth the time or the hassle.
summary: Leaks CO no matter what is done to prevent it

reviewText: These are awful- not universal at all. Universal would come with different size insert sleeves this is just one. Did not work on the D-shaped metal interior for whirlpool range, it had too large a D. Into the trash.
summary: These are awful- not universal at all. Universal would ...

reviewText: Seems odd that I would buy a Broan fan and filters together, and the filters would be for a completely different fan! Somebody please tell me why Amazon would add on filters that don't fit the product I bought! Money wasted!

The product I got was nothing like pictured. The filteri got had a few lines of aluminum n a single s Carbon Mesh-like filter sheet. The picture on Amazon shows a white cloth like fabric with strips to reveal when the filter needs to be replaced.

Poorly finished, easily bent (all four of the ones I received were bent to some degree) and--most importantly--there is no "locking notch."  Without this notch, the pans are free to short out against the surface units.  I believe these drip pans are unsafe.

It came in 3 pieces with a bag of hardware not easily put together. The product should come already assembled or say it requires assembly.  Unfortunately it didn't fit on my setup. The individual pieces seemed well made and returning it was not a complete refund

In 2011 after several replacement plastic latches failed I waited three years w/o buying another Sterlite. Same thing happened immediately just this week. Unbelievable. The latch is the identical piece of junk.

Distinct odor of burning plastic,.The receptacle did work,but the plastic used on this was obviously inferior to the original. THE OEM had raised ridges on the bottom .MAybe to help dissipate the heat?I feel ceramic units would be much better,
In heat lights they use ceramic so?

Just what the others have said. It will not fit over or into a 6"pipe...it's the same size as the pipe. Sending this back and going to order a lambro like I had but it failed after 2 yrs but at least it will be covered for another 2 hopefully. No good option for my vent.

JUNK IS TOO GOOD A WORD for this ice maker, nothing but problems. No service no repairs,  I was told at time of purchase if I used my Amazon credit card I would have an extended 1 year warranty NOT TRUE !Have been unable to even find anyone who knows how to repair  it. My fault NOT getting warranty in writting.

reviewText: purchased this for use on my boat.  NEVER MADE IT THERE. i set it up and went through a cleaning cycle. it never made for than 2 batches of ice with out having to be reset. Piece of junk.  returned it and bought one local at target for 100.00 less and it works fine.

reviewText: I purchased this a couple of years ago and tho it still freezes ice the metal plating on the posts that freeze the ice has started flaking off leaving the ice inedible. I have carefully followed manufacturers instructions on cleaning and ONLY used filtered water... very disappointed!!!

Have one of these; it got "permanently" stuck on add water during initial warranty period.  Had purchased enhanced warranty but still had to pay more to get a replacement icemaker.  have had replacement machine a month and it is stuck on "add water" just like earlier machine.  manufacturer requuires you to send back non-functioning machine to get anywhere. summary: have had replacement machine a month and it is stuck on "add water" just like earlier machine

reviewText: Was great for the first 10 months then went belly up. Looking on the internet, it appears the unit needs a new water pump - common problem.  Given that, we'll not be buying nor promoting this maker.  It's too bad, was killer color!
summary: Was great for the first 10 months then went belly up

reviewText: Just as long as you consider the product disposable if something goes wrong.... reviewText: Icemaker worked great for little over 6 months then suddenly quit. I believe pump failed. China Junk.  Called NewAir and put on hold for next available operator and then later told no one available to answer my call so leave message. Will not buy NewAir again.

bought this item and it quit after 90 days- sent back to manufacturer-- was returned saying it just needed to be cleaned-- worked for two weeks the quit again-- I will never buy a NewAir product ever again-- should have bought $200.00 worth of bagged ice

ya know got it in may died in sep what can i say bad quality no durability just like most crap you buy these days oh and can only get partial refund of maybe 2 bucks and i pay for shipping so to the dump it go's.

reviewText: Appears to be a "knock off" - not in the Moist AIr box that I'm used to, and you can tell someone physically cut this to the right size (probably from a big, cheap sheet of this knock-off humidifier filter material), as the entire edge was uneven all around.

reviewText:
Well I see many reviews like mine. 3inches to short My model is a Essick MA0800 needs MAF-2 Amazon site claims to fit as well as does the box. It Doesn't.
I added a piece of aluminum foil to close off the Grand Canyon sized gap. It will work.

The only upside to this filter for what it will fit is has a wire mesh to help support the fragile filter.

Not much else to say everyone else hasn't.

Don't buy. Your only getting the frame and steel mesh. Nothing is in between the steel mesh for filtration. Also frame came slightly bent and quality is flimsy. Item should not be listed as "vent filter" since you are only getting the steel frame and not the carbon cushions in between.
summary: Falsely advertised. Should be listed as "Filter frame"

reviewText: High setting is EXTREMELY LOUD! 8 sones LOUD (example is like heavy traffic but it sounds like jet engine). Standard candleabra bulbs, not included, concentrate light to back burners. Not sure if LED candleabra could be used or would even help.  On/off switches are small.

We bought this fan 4 years ago total waste of money all the parts except for the motor are cheap.
light and filter assembly is horrible, plastic parts that can not take heat and are brittle. Forget trying to keep it clean parts are sharp, definently was not designed by someone that understands cooking.
summary: We bought this fan 4 years ago total waste of money all the parts except for the motor ...

reviewText: The co. needs to provide much better connections to water supply and refrigerator; too easy for connections to fail.  After installation, with no sign of any leakage, the ref. connection failed (came apart) during the night causing considerable water damage to the dining room/kitchen floor and basement.  Do not recommend this product.

Wheels fell off. Forgot to call until the 2 years on parts expired.  The rack is covered for 5 years but the wheels are not considered part of the rack.

Defective parts.  Incredibly slow cycles.  And the drying doesn't work worth a d***,

Avoid

Our Maytag washer lasted four years. First the liquid dispeners quit dispensing and now it appears to have a broken pump. It builds up a disgusting amount of gunk around the door seal also. Pay the additional dollars and get the GE. At least it has a filter that protects the pump and it can be accessed from the front for periodic cleaning. BTW, the drier is made just as cheap. We find lint all over despite sealing the duct joints with tape. It takes forever to dry a load and its noisy.

Unreal, MAYTAG... thought they were supposed to be the industry standard. machine worked fine for a whle when all of a sudden the machine would give me a "3E" error code during the spin cycle. had a tech come out to look at it and he said it needed a new motor...

I agree with all the negitive reatings on this item. Over priced, brackets do not fit, and yes, I verified product item number prior to ordering due to others comments on here. This stack kit does not fit for our new Duet WFW70HEBW1 washer and WED70HEBW0 dryer set. As other reviewers have stated we will figure out a work-around.

The dryer rack wasn't  even able to support one nearly dry bed pillow and came crashing down, breaking apart almost instantly. I have since reglued its legs back on and fixed the cracked spring housing(which was cracked upon receipt). Maybe I'll try it without anything on it at all. But then, what would the point of that be? Was really looking forward to using a dryer rack during wet winter weather.
summary: Fell apart the first time I used it

Absolutely suck and do not resemble the pictures . there are a fin style that fall apart due to poor glue. waste energy by not allowing water to evaporate quickly. does not fit properly as well. Don't bother buying waste of time.

reviewText: As others have noted, this redesigned filter does not pass water on my older GE refrigerator.  No filtered water for dispenser until filter removed and bypass installed.  The issue appears to be in the redesigned hole pattern on the filter but could be that the new filters require a higher delta P across them to flow, either way, it was a waste of money for me.
summary: Does not work with GE Model #PCF25PGWA

reviewText: We opened the box and the filter had marred marks around the point of connection like it has been used before.
